Hello guys,

I found the root cause of our CI failures [1][2] in this heat regression that is kind of breaking support with older versions of nova compute API microversions (<= 2.63)

I think we should first check the microversion is being used by the nova client before deciding which property to use for server group creation:

 if (compute_api_microversion < 2.64):
     properties = {policies: [policy],
                   rules: ...}
 else:
     properties = {policy: policy,
                   rules: ...}

What is triggering the failure after reverted heat change is the heat.conf special configuration [3] being used by failing jobs.

[1] https://zuul.openstack.org/builds?job_name=devstack-tobiko-minimal
[2] https://zuul.opendev.org/t/openstack/build/a92fa1745d2c4c4ead2c43921b591c66/console
[3] https://opendev.org/x/devstack-plugin-tobiko/src/branch/master/zuul.d/devstack-tobiko-minimal.yaml#L69-L71

